global.ampeg_attack_oncc100: 0.3 //The default but for the legato regions it's set to 0.5 in the mapping files
global.lfo01_freq: 2 //Any slower than this sounds really lousy
global.lfo01_freq_oncc112: 7 //About as fast as vibrato on double bass can go, faster is just silly
global.eq1_freq: 2000 //Also can send this LFO to EQ, together with the tremolo it can simulate varying bow pressure while playing with heavy vibrato
global.eq1_gain: -5 //So it ends up zero with mod wheel in the middle
global.lfo01_eq1gain_oncc114: 4 //Don't want this to sound too synthetic, so max amount is small
global.lfo02_freq: 0.01 //Basically no movement at very slow speeds, just randomization
global.lfo02_freq_oncc117: 1 //Max rate is not very high, so it doesn't sound too obvious
global.lfo2_freq_lfo1_oncc119: 3 //Affect the rate of the other LFO for unsteady vibrato
global.eq1_gain_oncc1: 10 //Same EQ band as used for vibrato color, significant gain
global.eq3_freq: 100 //And we boost lows with low mod wheel, cut with high mod wheel to make quiet notes warmer, again a pretty big boost/cut
global.eg06_level1: 0 //When this is 0, the envelope really does nothing
global.loop_mode: loop_sustain //Since all samples used by this sfz file are looped for infinite sustain, this can be set global
